	<text>
		<body>
			<div type="entry">
				<pb facs="https://leaf.bucknell.edu/sites/default/files/2026-01/diary54.jpg"/>
				<dateline><date>April 2 Tuesday</date></dateline>
				<p><note>Linn seems to have misdated this entry. In 1862 April 2nd fell on a
						Wednesday.</note>
					<name key="Positive" type="Weather">Bright and warm</name>. We were ordered out
					somewhere about nine or ten o'clock to go down &amp; receive the <orgName
						role="Military">2nd Maryland </orgName> &amp; marched to <placeName
						role="River">the river</placeName>, &amp; lay there until near one o'clock,
					when <persName key="Jesse Reno" role="Soldier" cert="high"
						ref="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/BucknellDSC/jmlinn/refs/heads/main/jmlinn_personography.xml#jmlper086"
						type="real">Gen. Reno</persName> reviewed us, &amp; told us to go back to
						<placeName role="Military camp">camp</placeName>. After the dress parade, we
					were ordered to move to <placeName role="Near the river">the other side of the
						river</placeName> in the morning. We have received 4 regts <orgName
						role="Military">103 &amp; 13 New York</orgName>, <orgName role="Military"
						>2nd Maryland</orgName> &amp; <orgName role="Military">17 Mass</orgName>. We
					feel some regret about leaving our camp, now that we just been cleverly fixed.
					It is probable that the rebels have not more than 15.000 men at <placeName
						key="Kingston" role="Town" cert="high"
						ref="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/BucknellDSC/jmlinn/refs/heads/main/jmlinn_gazetteer.xml#linnpl048"
							>Kingston</placeName>, &amp;
					if they give us a few days, they can't faze us. <persName key="Charles Merrill"
						role="Soldier" cert="high"
						ref="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/BucknellDSC/jmlinn/refs/heads/main/jmlinn_personography.xml#jmlper020"
						type="real">Chas. Merrill</persName> &amp; <persName key="Warner"
						role="Soldier" cert="high"
						ref="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/BucknellDSC/jmlinn/refs/heads/main/jmlinn_personography.xml#jmlper141"
						type="real">Warner</persName> were promoted to Corporals today, and
						<persName key="Aaron Smith" role="Soldier" cert="high"
						ref="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/BucknellDSC/jmlinn/refs/heads/main/jmlinn_personography.xml#jmlper006"
						type="real">Aaron Smith</persName> to the vacant Serjeantry.</p>
			</div>
